Female in alcohol ( Paratype , figs 1 B, 1 E). In all details like male except the following: Prosoma elongated oval. Body length 9.86 . Prosoma length 4.78 , width (at the middle) 3.37 . Opisthosoma length 5.08 , width (at the middle) 3.65 . Eye diameters: AME 0.18 . ALE 0.14 . PME 0.15 . PLE 0.16 . Eye interdistances: AME–AME 0.13 . AME–ALE 0.06 . AME–PME 0.28 . PME–PME 0.24 . PME–PLE 0.12 . Clypeus height at AME 0.39 , at ALE 0.36 . Length of chelicerae 1.67 . Measurements of palp and legs: Palp 5.18 [ 1.45 , 0.76 , 1.12 , -, 1.85 ], I 12.40 [ 3.38 , 1.48 , 2.91 , 2.88 , 1.75 ], II 11.55 [ 3.29 , 1.37 , 2.64 , 2.63 , 1.62 ], III 11.16 [ 3.16 , 1.34 , 2.45 , 2.92 , 1.29 ], IV 15.83 [ 4.16 , 1.61 , 3.58 , 4.76 , 1.72 ]. Leg formula: 4123 . Spination. Palp: femur do 2 rl 1 , patella pl 1 do 2 , tibia pl 2 do 2 , tarsus pl 2 plv 1 rl 1 rlv 1 ; legs: femora I–II pl 2 do 3 rl 1 , III–IV pl 2 do 3 rl 2 ; patellae I–IV spineless; tibiae I–II plv 3 rlv 3 , III pl 2 plv 2 do 1 rl 2 rlv 2 vt 2 , IV pl 1 plv 2 do 1 rl 2 rlv 2 vt 2 ; metatarsi I–II plv 2 rlv 2 , III–IV pl 3 plv 3 rl 3 rlv 3 vt 1 ; tarsi I–IV spineless. Epigynum (
